  "prompt": "Which are the best Hollywood movies based on history?",
  "response": "There are many Hollywood movies that effectively portray historical events and figures, blending entertainment with education. Here are some of the best Hollywood movies based on history:\n\n1. **Schindler's List (1993)** - Directed by Steven Spielberg, this harrowing film tells the true story of Oskar Schindler, a businessman who saved over a thousand Jewish refugees during the Holocaust.\n\n2. **12 Years a Slave (2013)** - Based on Solomon Northup's memoir, this film depicts his kidnapping and sale into slavery in the pre-Civil War United States.\n\n3. **Gladiator (2000)** - While not entirely accurate in its historical depiction, this film showcases the Roman Empire's political intrigue and gladiatorial games, focusing on the story of Maximus Decimus Meridius.\n\n4. **The Pianist (2002)** - Directed by Roman Polanski, this film is based on the autobiography of Polish-Jewish pianist W\u0142adys\u0142aw Szpilman and his survival during the Holocaust.\n\n5. **Braveheart (1995)** - This epic historical drama depicts the life of Scottish knight William Wallace and his struggles against English oppression, although it takes liberties with historical accuracy.\n\n6. **Apollo 13 (1995)** - A tense retelling of the ill-fated 1970 lunar mission, this film emphasizes the ingenuity and teamwork that brought the astronauts home safely.\n\n7. **Dunkirk (2017)** - Christopher Nolan's war film chronicles the evacuation of British and Allied troops from Dunkirk, France, during World War II, showcasing the bravery and desperation of those involved.\n\n8. **Lincoln (2012)** - Directed by Steven Spielberg, this film focuses on President Abraham Lincoln's efforts to pass the Thirteenth Amendment to abolish slavery during the American Civil War.\n\n9. **Milk (2008)** - This biographical film tells the story of Harvey Milk, the first openly gay elected official in California, highlighting his activism and the fight for LGBTQ rights in the 1970s.\n\n10. **The King's Speech (2010)** - This film follows King George VI's struggle with a speech impediment and his journey to find his voice during a crucial time in British history.\n\nThese films vary in their adherence to historical accuracy, but they all provide compelling narratives that invite viewers to engage with significant historical events and figures.",
